<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Prothallus not seen. Thallus greenish-grey with green flecks, continuous, ca. 0.1-0.3 mm thick. Perithecia 0.12-0.32 mm, immersed, leaving deep pits in the rock; ca. 80-100 perithecia/cm2. Involucrellum absent. Exciple ca. 0.27-0.41 mm in diam., higher than broad, often pear-shaped, wall dark brown. Periphysoids ca. 40-60 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-2.5 mm, branched-anastomosing. Asci 85-106 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
25-29 mm, 8-spored. Ascospores 0-septate, 18-23 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
12-14 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The species differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. viridula" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="viridula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. viridula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by shorter spores and absence of an involucrellum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
